        "descriptions": [
          {
            "lang": "en",
            "value": "Nintendo Wii U OS 5.5.5 allows man-in-the-middle attackers to forge SSL certificates as though they came from a Root CA, because there is a secondary verification mechanism that only checks whether a CA is known and ignores the CA details and signature (and because * is accepted as a Common Name)."
          },
          {
            "lang": "es",
            "value": "Nintendo Wii U OS 5.5.5 permite a los atacantes intermediarios falsificar certificados SSL como si vinieran de una CA raíz, porque existe un mecanismo de verificación secundario que solo verifica si se conoce una CA e ignora los detalles de la CA y firma (y porque * se acepta como nombre común)."
          }
        ],
